# CodeAlpha Data Analytics Internship - Task 1: Web Scraping

## Project Description

This project demonstrates web scraping using Python. The script extracts internal Wikipedia article links from the "Web Scraping" Wikipedia page and stores the collected data in a structured CSV file.

## Objective

The objective of this project is to:

* Learn web scraping fundamentals.
* Extract data from web pages using Python.
* Understand HTML structure and hyperlink extraction.
* Create a dataset for further analysis.

## Technologies Used

* Python
* Requests
* BeautifulSoup (bs4)
* Pandas

## Data Source

Wikipedia Article:
https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Web_scraping

## Features

* Sends an HTTP request to the target webpage.
* Parses HTML content using BeautifulSoup.
* Extracts article titles and corresponding Wikipedia links.
* Converts extracted data into a Pandas DataFrame.
* Saves the dataset as a CSV file.
* Automatically creates the destination folder if it does not exist.

## Output

The generated CSV file contains:

| Column Name | Description                       |
| ----------- | --------------------------------- |
| Title       | Name of the Wikipedia article     |
| Link        | Full URL of the Wikipedia article |

Example:

| Title         | Link                                        |
| ------------- | ------------------------------------------- |
| Data scraping | https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Data_scraping |
| HTML          | https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/HTML          |

## Project Structure

├── web_scraping.py

├── scraped_data.csv

└── README.md

## How to Run

1. Install required libraries:
   pip install requests beautifulsoup4 pandas

2. Run the script:
   python web_scraping.py

3. The output file will be saved as:
   C:\CODEALPHA\TASK1\scraped_data.csv

## Learning Outcomes

* Web scraping using Requests and BeautifulSoup
* HTML parsing and navigation
* Data extraction and storage
* Creating structured datasets from web content

